U.K.’s OFT Seeks Ban on Upfront Fees to Credit Brokers, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-02T01:07:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/u-k-s-oft-seeks-ban-on-upfront-fees-to-credit-brokers-ft-says.html
The U.K.  Office of Fair Trading  wants
the government to introduce legislation prohibiting credit
brokers from charging customers an advance fee, as they often
promise introductions to lenders that don’t materialize, the
Financial Times reported, citing OFT Chief Executive Officer
 John Fingleton .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in  London  at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 